                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h6 class="text-primary">Email Protocols & Security</h6>
                            <div class="border-start border-primary border-3 ps-3 mb-3">
                                <p><strong>SMTP (Simple Mail Transfer Protocol)</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>Port 25 (unencrypted), 587 (STARTTLS), 465 (SSL/TLS)</li>
                                    <li>Used for sending emails between servers</li>
                                    <li>No built-in authentication or encryption</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>POP3 (Post Office Protocol v3)</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>Port 110 (unencrypted), 995 (SSL/TLS)</li>
                                    <li>Downloads emails to local device</li>
                                    <li>Emails deleted from server after download</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>IMAP (Internet Message Access Protocol)</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>Port 143 (unencrypted), 993 (SSL/TLS)</li>
                                    <li>Emails remain on server</li>
                                    <li>Supports multiple device synchronization</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h6 class="text-success">Email Authentication</h6>
                            <div class="border-start border-success border-3 ps-3 mb-3">
                                <p><strong>SPF (Sender Policy Framework)</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>DNS TXT record specifying authorized sending IPs</li>
                                    <li>Prevents email spoofing</li>
                                    <li>Example: "v=spf1 include:_spf.google.com ~all"</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>DKIM (DomainKeys Identified Mail)</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>Cryptographic signature in email headers</li>
                                    <li>Verifies email hasn't been tampered with</li>
                                    <li>Uses public/private key pairs</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>DMARC (Domain-based Message Authentication)</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>Policy framework using SPF and DKIM</li>
                                    <li>Specifies actions for failed authentication</li>
                                    <li>Provides reporting on email authentication</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
