                                    <li><strong>Anti-Spam Filters:</strong> Block unwanted emails</li>
                                    <li><strong>Anti-Malware Scanning:</strong> Detect malicious attachments</li>
                                    <li><strong>Data Loss Prevention (DLP):</strong> Prevent data leakage</li>
                                    <li><strong>Email Encryption:</strong> S/MIME, PGP protection</li>
                                    <li><strong>Sandboxing:</strong> Analyze attachments safely</li>
                                    <li><strong>User Training:</strong> Security awareness programs</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="alert alert-warning">
                        <h6><strong>📝 CISSP Exam Tips:</strong></h6>
                        <ul class="small mb-0">
                            <li>Remember the port numbers: SMTP (25/587/465), POP3 (110/995), IMAP (143/993)</li>
                            <li>SPF, DKIM, and DMARC work together for email authentication</li>
                            <li>Business Email Compromise (BEC) is a major threat to organizations</li>
                            <li>Email encryption can be at transport level (TLS) or message level (S/MIME/PGP)</li>
