            <!-- Wireless Security -->
            <div class="card mt-4">
                <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
                    <h5 class="mb-0">📶 Wireless Security (WEP/WPA)</h5>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h6 class="text-danger">WEP (Wired Equivalent Privacy)</h6>
                            <div class="border-start border-danger border-3 ps-3 mb-3">
                                <p><strong>Overview:</strong> Original 802.11 security protocol (1997)</p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li><strong>Key Length:</strong> 64-bit or 128-bit (actually 40-bit and 104-bit)</li>
                                    <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> RC4 stream cipher</li>
                                    <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Open System or Shared Key</li>
                                    <li><strong>IV (Initialization Vector):</strong> 24-bit, transmitted in plaintext</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong class="text-danger">Major Vulnerabilities:</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li><strong>Weak IV:</strong> Only 24-bit, causes key reuse</li>
                                    <li><strong>Static Keys:</strong> Same key for all users</li>
                                    <li><strong>No Key Management:</strong> Manual key distribution</li>
                                    <li><strong>CRC-32 Integrity:</strong> Easily manipulated</li>
                                    <li><strong>Crackable:</strong> Can be broken in minutes</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <div class="alert alert-danger small">
                                    <strong>Status:</strong> Deprecated and insecure. Should never be used.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h6 class="text-success">WPA Evolution</h6>
                            <div class="border-start border-success border-3 ps-3 mb-3">
                                <p><strong>WPA (Wi-Fi Protected Access)</strong> - 2003</p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> TKIP (Temporal Key Integrity Protocol)</li>
                                    <li><strong>Key Management:</strong> Dynamic key generation</li>
                                    <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> 802.1X or PSK (Pre-Shared Key)</li>
                                    <li><strong>Integrity:</strong> Michael MIC (Message Integrity Check)</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>WPA2 (802.11i)</strong> - 2004</p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> AES-CCMP (Counter Mode CBC-MAC)</li>
                                    <li><strong>Key Length:</strong> 128-bit AES</li>
                                    <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> 802.1X (Enterprise) or PSK (Personal)</li>
                                    <li><strong>Integrity:</strong> Built into CCMP</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>WPA3</strong> - 2018</p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> AES-256 (Enterprise), AES-128 (Personal)</li>
                                    <li><strong>Key Exchange:</strong> SAE (Simultaneous Authentication of Equals)</li>
                                    <li><strong>Forward Secrecy:</strong> Protection against key compromise</li>
                                    <li><strong>Enhanced Open:</strong> Opportunistic Wireless Encryption (OWE)</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h6 class="text-primary">WPA/WPA2 Authentication Modes</h6>
                            <div class="border-start border-primary border-3 ps-3 mb-3">
                                <p><strong>Personal Mode (PSK)</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>Pre-Shared Key authentication</li>
                                    <li>Same passphrase for all users</li>
                                    <li>Suitable for home/small office</li>
                                    <li>No centralized authentication server</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>Enterprise Mode (802.1X)</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>RADIUS authentication server</li>
                                    <li>Individual user credentials</li>
                                    <li>EAP (Extensible Authentication Protocol)</li>
                                    <li>Dynamic key generation per session</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>Common EAP Methods:</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li><strong>EAP-TLS:</strong> Certificate-based, most secure</li>
                                    <li><strong>EAP-TTLS:</strong> Tunneled TLS with inner authentication</li>
                                    <li><strong>PEAP:</strong> Protected EAP with TLS tunnel</li>
                                    <li><strong>EAP-FAST:</strong> Flexible Authentication via Secure Tunneling</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h6 class="text-warning">Wireless Security Best Practices</h6>
                            <div class="border-start border-warning border-3 ps-3 mb-3">
                                <p><strong>Configuration Security:</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>Use WPA3 or WPA2 (never WEP)</li>
                                    <li>Strong passphrases (20+ characters)</li>
                                    <li>Disable WPS (Wi-Fi Protected Setup)</li>
                                    <li>Change default admin credentials</li>
                                    <li>Regular firmware updates</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>Network Architecture:</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>Guest network isolation</li>
                                    <li>VLAN segmentation</li>
                                    <li>MAC address filtering (limited security)</li>
                                    <li>Disable SSID broadcast (security by obscurity)</li>
                                    <li>Reduce transmission power</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>Monitoring & Detection:</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small">
                                    <li>Wireless IDS/IPS deployment</li>
                                    <li>Rogue access point detection</li>
                                    <li>Regular security assessments</li>
                                    <li>Site surveys and coverage analysis</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6><strong>📝 CISSP Exam Tips:</strong></h6>
                        <ul class="small mb-0">
                            <li><strong>WEP is broken:</strong> 24-bit IV, RC4 vulnerabilities, static keys</li>
                            <li><strong>WPA improvements:</strong> TKIP, dynamic keys, Michael MIC</li>
                            <li><strong>WPA2 standard:</strong> AES-CCMP encryption, 802.11i specification</li>
